cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses improving the throughput of concurrent kernel executions on GPUs in shared environments such as clusters and clouds.
- cs.PF (Performance) is also likely as the paper proposes a runtime system with dynamic slicing and scheduling techniques to improve performance.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper focuses on improving the utilization of GPU resources.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the slicing of GPU kernels and the development of a performance model to guide scheduling decisions.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a runtime system for scheduling and executing GPU kernels.
